import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='ignore')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = sns.lineplot(x='date', y='rate', data=data)
    ax.set(xlabel='Year', ylabel='Unemployment Rate')
    ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
    plt.title('What is the overall trend of unemployment rates across all industries from 2000 to 2010?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='ignore')
    year = 2000
    year_data = data[data['year'] == year]
    year_data = year_data.sort_values(by='rate', ascending=False)
    year_data = year_data.head(20)
    chart = sns.barplot(x='series', y='rate', data=year_data)
    chart.set_xticklabels(chart.get_xticklabels(), rotation=90)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        chart.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('Which industry had the highest unemployment rate in ' + str(year) + '?', wrap=True)
    plt.axhline(y=year_data['rate'].max(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Max rate: {:.2f}'.format(year_data['rate'].max()))
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y')
    year = data['year'].dt.year.unique()[0]
    sns.histplot(data=data[data['year'] == year], x='rate', kde=True)
    plt.xlabel('Unemployment Rate')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of unemployment rates across all industries in ' + str(year) + '?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='ignore')
    industry = data['series'].unique()[0]
    sns.scatterplot(x='count', y='rate', data=data[data['series'] == industry])
    plt.xlabel('Number of Unemployed People')
    plt.ylabel('Unemployment Rate')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the correlation between the number of unemployed people and the unemployment rate in the {} industry?'.format(industry), wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
